ylvania organized by the editors. In offering a variety of perspectives on the Menexenus, the volume is the very first of its kind in any language. In addition, the volume contains an up-to-date bibliography of scholarship in English, French, German, and Italian. This makes the book a definitive guide and ideal starting point for advanced students and scholars looking for further information about the dialogue.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aRhetoricxPhilosophy. 0aRhetoric, Ancient. 4aGefallenenrede. 4aGeschichtsschreibung. 4aMenexenos. 4aPlaton. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aMenexenus.  aPlato.  afuneral oration.  ahistoriography.1 aHelmer, Étienne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKahn, Charles H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarrin, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPappas, Nickolas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParker, Harold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParker, Harold, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRobinson, Clifford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobitzsch, Jan Maximilian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobitzsch, Jan Maximilian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTurner, Jeffrey S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZelcer, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1z978311076248808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTit